### Website API Testing
### Base URL: http://localhost:3000

### 1. CREATE - Add a new website
POST http://localhost:3000/api/websites
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Google",
    "url": "https://www.google.com",
    "description": "Search engine website",
    "category": "search",
    "scrapeFrequency": "daily",
    "isActive": true,
    "metadata": {
        "priority": "high",
        "tags": ["search", "popular"]
    }
}

###

### 2. CREATE - Add another website
POST http://localhost:3000/api/websites
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "GitHub",
    "url": "https://github.com",
    "description": "Code hosting platform",
    "category": "development",
    "scrapeFrequency": "weekly",
    "isActive": true
}

###

### 3. CREATE - Test duplicate URL (should fail)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/websites
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Google Duplicate",
    "url": "https://www.google.com",
    "description": "This should fail"
}

###

### 4. READ - Get all websites
GET http://localhost:3000/api/websites

###

### 5. READ - Get websites with pagination
GET http://localhost:3000/api/websites?page=1&limit=5

###

### 6. READ - Get websites by category
GET http://localhost:3000/api/websites?category=search

###

### 7. READ - Get active websites only
GET http://localhost:3000/api/websites?isActive=true

###

### 8. READ - Get websites with sorting
GET http://localhost:3000/api/websites?sortBy=name&sortOrder=asc

###

### 9. READ - Get a single website by ID (replace {id} with actual ID)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/websites/{id}

###

### 10. UPDATE - Update a website (replace {id} with actual ID)
PUT http://localhost:3000/api/websites/{id}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Google Search",
    "description": "Updated description for Google",
    "category": "search-engine",
    "scrapeFrequency": "weekly",
    "isActive": true
}

###

### 11. UPDATE - Deactivate a website (replace {id} with actual ID)
PUT http://localhost:3000/api/websites/{id}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "isActive": false
}

###

### 12. PATCH - Update scrape data (replace {id} with actual ID)
PATCH http://localhost:3000/api/websites/{id}/scrape
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "scrapedData": {
        "title": "Google",
        "metaDescription": "Search the world's information",
        "links": 150,
        "images": 20,
        "scrapedAt": "2026-02-04T18:00:00Z"
    }
}

###

### 15a. POST - Trigger manual scrape (STATIC mode)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/websites/{id}/scrape-trigger
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "mode": "static"
}

###

### 15b. POST - Trigger manual scrape (SELENIUM mode)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/websites/{id}/scrape-trigger
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "mode": "selenium"
}

###

### 13. DELETE - Delete a website (replace {id} with actual ID)
DELETE http://localhost:3000/api/websites/{id}

###

### 14. DELETE - Bulk delete websites (replace IDs with actual IDs)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/websites/bulk-delete
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "ids": [
        "65f1234567890abcdef12345",
        "65f1234567890abcdef12346"
    ]
}

